ParaDef.Info: Match the users with the specified string. -
Include information. The value is in text format. The value ranges from 1 to 200.
Displays information about the access users with specified user name. The value is a string of 1 to 253 characters.

Displays information about access users whose user names contain spaces.If user names contain spaces, enclose the user names with double quotation marks ("") to carry the. match-quote-context keyword and check user information based on the user names.The. match-quote-context keyword can be associated only when user names are enclosed using double quotation marks (""). -

Displays information about online users based on a specified accounting state. idle: Displays information about online users in the idle accounting state.ready: Displays information about online users in the ready accounting state.accounting: Displays information about online users for whom accounting is being performed.leaving-flow-query: Displays information about online users whose offline traffic is being queried during the logout process.wait-acct-start: Displays information about online users whose offline traffic is being queried during the logout process.wait-acct-stop: Displays information about online users waiting for an Accounting Stop response from the RADIUS server. -
Displays information about the access users who owe fees. -

Displays information about the access users who use the specified Radius server group. The value is a string of 1 to 32 characters, including characters A to Z and a to z (case-sensitive), numerals (0 to 9), punctuation mark (.), dash (-), and underline (_).
Displays information about the access users who are authenticated by the web authentication server with a specified IPv4 address. The value is in dotted decimal notation.
Web-auth-server ipv6 address. The value is a 32-digit hexadecimal number, in the format of X:X:X:X:X:X:X:X.
Displays information about the access users with abnormal traffic rates. -

Displays the users whose real-time upstream traffic rate is greater than or equal to the specified rate. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967295, in kbyte/min. When ui-mode type2 is configured, the unit is kbit/s.

Displays the users whose real-time downstream traffic rate is greater than or equal to the specified rate. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967295, in kbyte/min. When ui-mode type2 is configured, the unit is kbit/s.
Value of high. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967295.
Value of low. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967295.

Displays the users whose real-time upstream traffic rate is less than the specified rate. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967295, in kbyte/min. When ui-mode type2 is configured, the unit is kbit/s.

Displays the users whose real-time downstream traffic rate is less than the specified rate. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967295, in kbyte/min. When ui-mode type2 is configured, the unit is kbit/s.
Displays information about users whose traffic is light in many statistics collection periods. -
Interval. The value is an integer ranging from 1 to 525600.
Online user with the specified link-account information. -
Online user with the specified link-account information. The value is an integer ranging from 1 to 240.
Displays information about users with a destination address accounting service type. -
Displays information about users with a specified service policy. The value is a string of 1 to 200 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.
Specifies the ID of the slot where a board resides. The value is a string of 1 to 15 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.
Specifies a subcard ID. The subcard ID range is determined by the device model. The value is a string of 0 to 65535 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.
Displays information about online users in the specified domain. The value is a string of 1 to 64 case-insensitive characters.
Displays information about online users in a specified mapping domain. The value is a string of 1 to 64 case-insensitive characters.

Displays information about online user bound to the specified VPN instance. The value is a string of 1 to 31 case-sensitive characters. If spaces are used, the string must start and end with double quotation marks (").
Displays information about online users who use the specified LAC tunnel to access the LNS. The value is a string of 1 to 253 characters.
Displays information about online users on the tunnel with a specified source IP address on the LNS. The value is in dotted decimal notation.
Displays information about the online users in a specified time period. The value ranges from 1 to 7200, in seconds.
Displays information about the online users in a specified option37. -
Displays information about online users with specified qos profile. The value is a string of 1 to 63 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.
Displays information about online users in a specified user group. The value is a string of 1 to 32 characters.
Displays information about online users in a specified IPv4 address pool. The value is a string of 1 to 128 case-insensitive characters.
Displays information about online users in a specified IPv4 address pool group. The value is a string of 1 to 128 case-insensitive characters.
Displays information about online users in a specified IPv6 address pool. The value is a string of 1 to 32 characters.
Displays information about online users on the tunnel with a specified lns IP address on the LAC. The value is in dotted decimal notation.
Public IP address of a CGN user. The value is in dotted decimal notation.
Displays information about online CGN public network users. -
Displays information about online DHCP CGN public network users. -
Displays information about online non-DHCP CGN public network users. -
Displays information about users of a specified NAT instance. -
NAT instance name. The value is a string of 1 to 31 characters.
Displays information about online users matching a specific traffic classifier. The value is a string of 1 to 127 characters.
Displays information about users with a specified access type. -
Displays information about online users with RADIUS attributes delivered by the RADIUS server. -
Displays information about online users with the No. 22 RADIUS attribute Framed-Route. -
Displays information about online users with the No. 9 RADIUS attribute Framed-IP-Netmask. - -

layer2-leased-line: Displays information about Layer2 leased line online users. l2vpn-leased-line: Displays information about L2-vpn leased line online users. layer3-leased-line: Displays information about Layer3 leased line online users. layer2-static: Displays information about Layer 2 static online users. layer3-static: Displays information about Layer 3 static online users. lts: Displays information about LTS online users. lac-tunnel: Displays information about LAC tunnel online users. lns-tunnel: Displays information about LNS tunnel online users. eap-relay: Displays information about EAP relay online users. eap-end: Displays information about EAP end online users. -

Displays information about online users through an authentication mode. none: Displays information about online users without being authenticated. local: Displays information about online users through the local authentication. radius: Displays information about online users through a RADIUS server authentication. hwtacacs: Displays information about online users through an HWTACACS server authentication. radius-proxy: Displays information about online users through an HWTACACS server authentication. -
Displays information about the non-RUI access users. -
Displays information about RUI users who go online with IP addresses assigned from a local address pool. -
Displays information about RUI users who go online with IP addresses assigned from a remote address pool. -
Displays information about users whose user status is master. -
Displays information about users whose user status is slave. -
Displays information about online users with specified family profile. The value is a string of 1 to 63 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.
Displays information about online users that user queue resources fail to be allocated. -

Displays information about online users with the specified ip address type. ipv4: Displays information about online ipv4 users. ipv6: Displays information about online ipv6 users. dual-stack: Displays information about online dual-stack users. -

Displays information about online users that obtain IPv6 addresses using a specified protocol. nd: Displays information about online users that obtain IPv6 addresses using an ND protocol. dhcpv6: Displays information about online users that obtain IPv6 addresses using an DHCPv6 protocol. -

Displays information about online users with a specified CPE mode. ipv6: Displays information about online users that use CPE to obtain IPv6 addresses. ipv6-pd: Displays information about online users that use CPE to obtain IPv6 prefixes. -
Displays information about online users on a specified interface. -

Displays information about the access users on a specified member interface of an Eth-Trunk interface. If you specify trunk-member, the command displays information about the access users on a member interface of an Eth-Trunk interface. If you do not specify trunk-member, the command displays information about the access users on an Eth-Trunk interface. The value is a string of 1 to 63 characters.
Displays information about the users that access the device through the interface and its sub-interfaces. This parameter is used after the interface number is configured. -

Displays information about the access users in the specified VLAN of an interface. The interface can be an Ethernet interface only. pevlan-id specifies the ID of a VLAN. When the value of pevlan-id is 0, user information that does not carrying VLAN IDs is displayed, including the administrator information. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4094.
Specifies the end VLAN ID of the outer VLAN range. end-pevlan-id must be greater than or equal to pevlan vlan-id. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4094.
Displays information about the access users in a specified inner VLAN on the interface. cevlan-id specifies the ID of a inner VLAN. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4094.
Specifies the end VLAN ID of the outer VLAN range. end-cevlan-id must be greater than or equal to cevlan vlan-id. The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4094.

Displays access user information based on PE VLAN IDs and CE VLAN IDs in ascending order. A PE VLAN ID takes precedence over a CE VLAN ID. If this parameter is not specified, the access user information is displayed based on CIDs in ascending order. The earlier a user accesses the device, the smaller the user's CID is. -

Displays information about access users in a specified state. If standby is configured, information about users in the standby state is displayed. If active is configured, information about users in the active state is displayed. -
Specify the next traffic policy of the flow. The value is a string of 1 to 127 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.
Displays verbose information about access users. -
Displays abnormal offline records about a user. During record displaying, you do not need to enter Y or N to check whether to display the next record. -
Displays summary information about access users, including the total number of access users, the number of RUI access users, and the number of non-RUI access users. -
Displays information about online user, including user id, user name, interface, user mac address, user ip address, or user ipv6 address. -

Displays access user information as specified. ipv6-address: displays the ipv6-address field in access user information.vlanpvc: displays the vlanpvc field in access user information.slot: displays the slot field in access user information.access-time: displays the access-time field in access user information.access-type: displays the access-type field in access user information.accounting-state: displays the accounting-state field in access user information.qos-profile: displays the qos-profile field in access user information.family-qos-profile: displays the family-qos-profile field in access user information.accounting-start-time: displays the accounting-start-time field in access user information.down-packets-number: displays the down-packets-number field in access user information.inbound-cir: displays the inbound-cir field in access user information.lac-info : displays the lac-info field in access user information.lns-info : displays the lns-info field in access user information.online-time: displays the online-time field in access user information.outbound-cir: displays the outbound-cir field in access user information.portal-url : displays the portal-url field in access user information.radius-authen-server: displays the radius-authen-server field in access user information.up-packets-number: displays the up-packets-number field in access user information.edsg-policy: displays the edsg-policy field in access user information.web-url : displays the web-url field in access user information.radius-flag : displays the radius-flag field in access user information. -
Number of packets sent by users. -
Specifies the number of abnormal offline records to be displayed. The value is an integer that ranges from 1 to 4294967295.

Examples: If flow info contain l2-head : Yes
Are you sure to display some information?[Y/N]:
UserID Username Interface IP address MAC
UserID Username Interface IP address MAC
ExtraInfo: Usage Scenario To view the information about the access users or locate the user access fault, you can run the display access-user command to view the information about all access users. You can also view information about access users on the device by specifying the domain name, interface name, user name, and so on. In detailed information about access users, (Radius) is displayed for each attribute delivered by the RADIUS server. Precautions The display access-user light-traffic-user command displays information about users with abnormal traffic. In the physical RUI scenario, the traffic statistics reported by the backup device is always 0. Therefore, all users on the backup device are users with abnormal traffic. As such, you cannot run this command to query information about users based on actual user traffic.
